{"parse":{"title":"music","pageid":2038,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Music|Musić|music|músic|müziç|mùșic}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n{{wikiquote}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|en|musick|musicke|musique|musike}} (obsolete)\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|en|ine-pro|*men- (think)}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|musik}}, {{m|enm|musike}}, borrowed from {{der|en|xno|musik}}, {{m|fro|musike}}, {{der|en|fro|musique}}, and their source {{der|en|la|mūsica}}, from {{der|en|grc|μουσική}}, from {{der|en|grc|Μοῦσα||Muse}}, an Ancient Greek deity of the arts. {{surf|en|muse|-ic|t2=pertaining to}}. In this sense, displaced native {{cog|ang|drēam||music}}, whence {{w|Modern English}} {{m|en|dream}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|myo͞oʹzĭk|a=UK}} {{IPA|en|/ˈmjuː.zɪk/}}\n** {{audio|en|En-uk-music.ogg|a=RP}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈmju.zɪk/|a=GA}}\n** {{audio|en|En-us-music.ogg|a=GA}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈmjʉ.zɪk/|a=Scotland,NI,AU}}\n* {{hyphenation|en|mus|ic}}\n* {{rhymes|en|uːzɪk|s=2}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|-|s}}\n\n# A [[series]] of [[sound#Noun|sounds]] [[organize]]d in [[time#Noun|time]], usually [[employ#Verb|employing]] some [[combination]] of [[harmony]], [[melody]], [[rhythm]], [[tempo]], etc., often to [[convey]] a [[mood]].\n#: {{ux|en|I keep listening to this '''music''' because it’s a masterpiece.}}\n#* {{RQ:Congreve Mourning Bride|page=1|passage='''Muſick''' has Charms to ſooth a ſavage Breaſt, / To ſoften Rocks, or bend a knotted Oak.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2013-11-22|author=Ian Sample|volume=189|issue=24|page=32|magazine=The Guardian Weekly|title=Music lessons in early childhood may improve brain's performance|url=http://www.theguardian.com/science/2013/nov/12/music-lessons-early-childhood-brain-performance|passage='''Music''' lessons in early childhood lead to changes in the brain that could improve its performance far into adulthood, researchers say.}}\n# {{lb|en|figuratively}} Any [[interesting#Adjective|interesting]] or [[pleasing#Adjective|pleasing]] sounds.\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1856|author=John Esten Cooke|title=The Virginia Comedians|url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/virginia-comedians-or-old-days-in-the-old-dominion-edited-from-the-mss-of-c-effingham-esq-or-rather-written-by-john-esten-cooke/oclc/559686172|page=247|text=“Oh! this was very kind,” she said, with that simplicity and tenderness, which at times made her voice pure '''music''', “I could not have expected you so soon.”}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=19 Aug 78|volume=6|number=5|journal=Gay Community News|page=15|author=Kevin Warren|title=A Flawless Production|text=Wilson's definite genius for rapid, witty dialogue which becomes a kind of conversational '''music''' at times.}}\n# {{senseid|en|Q638}}An [[art form]], [[create]]d by organizing [[pitch#Noun|pitch]], rhythm, and sounds made using [[musical instrument]]s and/or [[singing#Noun|singing]].\n# A [[guide#Noun|guide]] to [[play#Verb|playing]] or [[sing#Verb|singing]] a particular [[tune#Noun|tune]]; [[sheet music]].\n# {{lb|en|military|slang}} [[electronic|Electronic]] [[signal#Noun|signal]] [[jamming#Noun|jamming]].\n# {{lb|en|US|slang|dated}} [[heated#Adjective|Heated]] [[argument#Noun|argument]].\n# {{lb|en|US|slang|dated}} [[fun|Fun]]; [[amusement]].\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|en|melody}}\n* {{l|en|vibe}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col4|en|absolute music\n|abstract music|functional music|music cassette\n|alternative music\n|ambient music| Music City\n|antimusic\n|art music\n|background music\n|ballet music\n|banku music\n|beautiful music\n|biomusic\n|bumper music\n|Caribbean dance music|music desk\n|Celtic music\n|chamber music\n|champagne music\n|chart music\n|chin music\n|chipmusic\n|classical music\n|club music\n|cocktail music\n|concrete music\n|country music\n|country-western music\n|coworker music\n|dance music\n|danger music| drone music|old-time music\n|day the music died\n|devil in music\n|director of music\n|disco music\n|doujin music\n|electronic body music\n|electronic dance music\n|electronic music\n|elevator music\n|ethnic music\n|ethnomusic\n|eye music\n|face the music\n|fast food music\n|field music\n|fill music\n|folk music\n|found music\n|furniture music\n|gospel music\n|hate music\n|have Van Gogh's ear for music\n|hillbilly music\n|house music\n|incidental music\n|industrial music\n|intelligent dance music\n|janissary music\n|lift music\n|light music\n|lounge music\n|make beautiful music together\n|make music\n|marching music\n|march music\n|micromusic\n|mood music\n|mouth music\n|musicaholic\n|musical\n|musicality\n|musically\n|musicassette\n|musicaster\n|music box\n|music bread\n|music center\n|music centre\n|music chart\n|music demy\n|musicdisk\n|music frog\n|music game\n|music group\n|music hall\n|music house\n|musician,muso\n|musicing\n|musicker\n|musicless\n|musiclike\n|musicmaking\n|musicmonger\n|musicness\n|music notation\n|music of the spheres\n|musicography\n|musicologic\n|musicologist\n|musicology\n|musicon\n|musicophile\n|music paper\n|music pen\n|music room\n|musicscape\n|music school\n|music shell\n|music shop\n|music stand\n|music-stick\n|musicstick\n|music theory|when the music stops\n|music therapy\n|music to someone's ears\n|music video\n|music video game\n|music volute\n|musiczine\n|musivisual\n|New Age music\n|nonmusic\n|Original Pilipino Music\n|outsider music\n|piped music\n|pop music\n|popular music\n|production music\n|programme music\n|program music\n|punk music\n|race music\n|rap music\n|rock music\n|roots music\n|rough music\n|salon music\n|serial music\n|set to music\n|sewing-machine music\n|sheet music\n|snap music\n|soul music\n|studio music\n|techno music\n|theory of music\n|township music\n|trance music\n|trap music\n|what kind of music do you like\n|word music\n|world music\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|jam|myuuzik}}\n* {{desc|pih|myuusik}}\n* {{desc|tpi|musik}}\n* {{desc|dv|މިއުޒިކް|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ja|ミュージック|tr=myūjikku|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ms|muzik|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|sw|muziki|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|cy|miwsig|bor=1}}\